text: Charles Bell (1805 – 9 February 1869) was a British Conservative Party politician. He was elected MP for City of London in November 1868 but died just four months later in February 1869. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1805 births Category:1869 deaths Category:Conservative Party (UK) MPs for English constituencies Category:UK MPs 1868–1874
